The paper deals with the problem of video summarization, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. The use of neural networks for textual-visual semantic embedding suggests a focus on CV and natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which are typically found in the cs.CV and cs.CL sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of diversity and relevance labels, which suggests a focus on multimedia (MM) and machine learning (LG) techniques for classification and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.IR, followed by cs.MM, cs.CL, and cs.LG.
